Business Brief -- Blue Circle Industries PLC:
   Firm Sells Its 42.3% Stake
   In South African Subsidiary
BCI will receive 24.8 rand ($8.60) a share. In addition,
an extraordinary dividend totaling 11.0 rand a share will be
paid out of Blue Circle Ltd.'s reserves next month. The offer
will be extended to minority shareholders, BCI said.
   BCI said Blue Circle Ltd. had a book value of #33.8
million. It contributed #11.0 million to BCI's consolidated
operating profit in 1991, BCI said.